Think of the hexagonal grid in axial coordinates  

 E = ( +1 , 0 ) NE = ( +1 , –1 ) NW = ( 0 , –1 )  
 W = ( –1 , 0 ) SW = ( –1 , +1 ) SE = ( 0 , +1 )

Ring n (n = 0,1,2,…) is the set of cells whose “radius”  
max(|q|,|r|,|–q–r|) equals n.  
The greatest number in ring n is  

 L(n)=1+3 n(n+1)

so ring n starts with L(n–1)+1.

How the numbers are written in a ring  
Start cell S(n) = ( 1 , n–1 )            (the cell just east of the south-eastern corner)  
Edges (walk clockwise)

 0. NE length n–1  
 1. NW length n  
 2. W   length n  
 3. SW length n  
 4. SE length n  
 5. E  length n  

That gives 6n cells = the whole ring.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
1.  Which ring contains 2026?

L(25)=1+3·25·26 = 1951  L(26)=1+3·26·27 = 2107  
1951 < 2026 ≤ 2107   ⇒  2026 lies in ring n = 26.

Its index inside that ring is  
k = 2026 – (L(25)+1) = 2026 – 1952 = 74.         (indices start at 0)

--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.  Axial coordinates of 2026

Ring-26 data  
Edge-limits (indices)  
 NE : 0…25  NW : 26…51  W : 52…77  SW : 78…103  SE : 104…129  E : 130…155

74 lies on the W-edge, offset w = 74 – 52 = 22.

W-edge starts at ( 26 , –26 ); each step adds (–1,0).  
So the coordinates of 2026 are

 ( q , r ) = ( 26 – 22 , –26 ) = ( 4 , –26 )

--------------------------------------------------------------------
3.  Coordinates (and rings) of the six neighbours

E : ( 5 , –26 )  ring 26  
W : ( 3 , –26 )  ring 26  
NE: ( 5 , –27 )  ring 27  
NW: ( 4 , –27 )  ring 27  
SE: ( 4 , –25 )  ring 25  
SW: ( 3 , –25 )  ring 25  

--------------------------------------------------------------------
4.  Their indices and numbers

Ring 26 starts with 1952, edge-data as above   
• (5,–26): W-edge, offset 21 ⇒ k = 52+21 = 73 ⇒ 1952+73 = 2025  
• (3,–26): W-edge, offset 23 ⇒ k = 75     ⇒ 1952+75 = 2027  

Ring 25 starts with 1802, W-edge starts at k = 50  
• (4,–25): offset 21 ⇒ k = 71 ⇒ 1802+71 = 1873  
• (3,–25): offset 22 ⇒ k = 72 ⇒ 1802+72 = 1874  

Ring 27 starts with 2108, W-edge starts at k = 54  
• (5,–27): offset 22 ⇒ k = 76 ⇒ 2108+76 = 2184  
• (4,–27): offset 23 ⇒ k = 77 ⇒ 2108+77 = 2185  

--------------------------------------------------------------------
5.  Sum of the six neighbours

2025 + 2027 + 1873 + 1874 + 2184 + 2185 = 12168

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Answer: 12168
